main event: A yellow object was observed moving rapidly from east to west and making right angle turns in Presque Isle, Maine on July 30, 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for fifteen minutes and was covered by a thin, bright cloud cover.,The object changed its path abruptly, indicating high maneuverability.,Astronomy experts concluded it was likely a sighting of Venus based on its position.,This sighting is part of the Project Blue Book archives.,The report was submitted by Edward L. Bogart Jr.
sighted object: a yellow object covered by a bright cloud
